## Abstract

SCU•32 is a structural framework for modeling institutions, organizations, and complex systems as adaptive coherence-governed structures.

Rather than treating disciplines as isolated domains, SCU•32 proposes a unified architecture where observation, viability, emergence, and coherence operate as system-level regulatory principles.

The framework introduces mathematical, structural, and architectural models designed to analyze institutional drift, correction latency, and systemic stability.

SCU•32 aims to function as a foundational layer for Institutional Artificial Nervous Systems capable of supporting adaptive governance, decision systems, and complex organizational environments.
